sql:
SELECT COUNT(audit_id) AS audit_count
FROM record_audits
WHERE user_id = 0;

SELECT term_name
FROM terms
WHERE term_frequency = (SELECT MAX(term_frequency) FROM terms);

SELECT worker_name
FROM workers
WHERE worker_experience = (SELECT MIN(worker_experience) FROM workers);

SELECT term_name
FROM terms
ORDER BY term_frequency DESC, term_confidence DESC;

external_knowledge:
Top terms refer to those terms with the highest frequency in the dataset; 
Unique users are users with distinct identifiers who have accessed the records; 
Average trust score is not included in the final question, but it was used in the SQL query to provide additional data about the users accessing the records.
